result.execSummary:
The defendant April Lynn Vine was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Resisting an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. Defendant is to have NO CONFRONTATIONAL CONATCT with A. Dowler as named in the complaint. Defendant is to have NO CONTACT with D. Abraham unless with agent approval or through text message regarding the minor child in common.

Defendant is to comply with any rules/recommendations as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.   DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed. Defendant is to report to the Waushara County Sheriff's Department no later than December 11, 2015 to submit a DNA sample.

11:06 am cases called. 15CM339 & 15CM353. Defendant April Lynn Vine in court, by phone, with attorney Ben Szilagyi, in person.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court addresses defendant's request to appear by phone. Defendant waives right to personal appearnce. Court accepts waiver of right to personal appearance. Agreement stated on the record by ADA Anderson. Attorney Szilagyi concurs.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Guilty to Count 2 of 15CM339 & Guilty to Count 1 of 15CM353. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Count 1 of 15CM339 & Count 2 of 15CM353. No statement by defendant. Court sentences the defendant to: SWD and places on probation for a period of 18 months. If revoked, 2 days credit. CONDITIONS: AODA and follow through, Maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. No violent or confrontational contact with Amanda Dowler. No contact with Daniel Abraham unless with agent approval or through text message regarding their minor child in common.  Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Bond to be applied. DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court. Court directs the defendant to report no later than December 11, 2015 to submit a DNA sample to the Waushara County Sheriff's Department.   Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice.  Postconviction papers are to be filed within one week.
